Others: Quinton de Kock scored 65 runs against England, demonstrating excellent form.
South Africa's bowling attack, led by Anrich Nortje and Kagiso Rabada, performed well, with four bowlers taking at least one wicket.
David Miller once again showed his ability to rebuild and accelerate under pressure, scoring 43 off 28 before being dismissed.
Captain Ottneil Baartman demonstrated flexibility in his bowling changes, which may prove crucial in the latter stages of the competition.
